Hardware-neutral files:
ndos3.rel
netstat.com
netstat.rel
ntpdate.com	; requires that CP/NET be active
ntpdate.rel
snios000.rel

Files for Norberto's USB FT245R device
sniosusb.rel
ndos3-u.com
ntpdateu.com

Files for virtual CPNETDevice
snios3.rel
ndos3-v.com
ntpdatev.com

Files for MMS77422 adapter
snios422.rel
ntpdatem.com
ndos3-m.com

Typically, an adapter-specific COM file would be copied to a neutral name,
for example:

	PIP A:NTPDATE.COM=N:NTPDATEU.COM[OV]
	PIP A:NDOS3.COM=N:NDOS3-U.COM[OV]

The adapter-specific versions of NTPDATE can run in or out of CP/NET,
but require that the adapter hardware be present (as well as a server).
